reviewText: I was excited to hear Disney was going to release some of the best episodes of Lizzie McGuire on dvd, but I am upset about how they are going about it. The first thing that made me mad was the fact that there are only four episodes on each volume. In England, theres six. Also, The UK versions are in the order the episodes were filmed. In the UK, Disney will have eventually released the entire series on dvd. All 65 episodes. I hope Disney releases all the episodes on dvd in the U.S. And I expect more than just four episodes on volumes 3 and 4.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Unfortunately in the US, only half of Season 1 of Lizzie McGuire was released on DVD. It is very difficult to find the rest of the episodes on DVD, so these small compilation discs are the next best thing, even if they each only include 4 episodes. Volume 1 includes all the "fashion" and "appearance" related episodes of Lizzie McGuire, from both seasons.Episodes:Last Year's Model- Everyone at school treats Lizzie differently when she becomes a model for Teen Attitude magazine, including Gordo and MirandaBest Dressed For Much Less- Lizzie thinks the only way she can win Best Dressed at school is by buying an expensive pair of jeansJust Like Lizzie- a seventh grader at school views Lizzie as her "role model," to the point of dressing and talking exactly like LizzieOne of the Guys- Lizzie is concerned about being viewed as a "guy girl" when she starts playing flag football with the boys at schoolBonus features:The Lizzie McGuire Casting Session Game- take this quiz  to find out which Lizzie character you are most like

reviewText: Let's start with the name. I think the name "Lizzie McGuire" is very cute. It's a perfect name for her. Now little girl Lizzie looks cute, not as sophisticated as 14 - 15 year old Lizzie, but she can still dress with the best of them. Even that horrible unicorn sweater looks great on her. This DVD will contain that episode, and other great classics.
